The Department of Petroleum Resources (DPR) in Bayelsa state yesterday sealed two petrol stations and a Liquidified Petroleum Gas (LPG) station, over various offences, ranging from lack of operational license and lack of equipment. The DPR team led by the Chief Technical Officer in Bayelsa field office, Mr Obi Ifi, carried out an unscheduled visits to some retail petrol outlets in the state. Some of the filling stations sealed were: Carol Oil and Gas, South South Oil and Gas and Biobele Gas station, all in Yenagoa, Bayelsa state capital. According to DPR, the stations sealed for lack of equipment and their failure to renew licenses. It urged others to desist from such acts or face sanctions. Speaking with newsmen after the inspection exercise, Mr Ifi said the exercise was a routine one, aimed at making operators comply with the agencyâ€™s directives. Fuel crisis: DPR seals five petrol stations in Bayelsa DPR seals 24 petrol stations in Jos DPR to begin night surveillance of petrol stations in Kogi Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin